Easy Search 0.1
===========

Introduction
============

  When i was creating search form i get bored because this is a very repetitive task, and because that i start to create this plugin, this first version is the very basic but by now this is enough, and i will improve this, and if you have some suggestion please let me know this.

Rails
=====

  This first version was created and tested with Rails 2.3.5.

How to install
==============

  ./script/plugin install git@github.com:brunofrank/easy_search.git

Example
=======

  # Migrations 

  create_table :products do |t|
    t.string :description, :null => false
    t.integer :size, :null => false
  end

  # Controller
	
  def index
    # Replace the all for search and pass the param if the param is null it will return all.
    @users = User.search params[:query] 
  end

  # Models

  class Product < ActiveRecord::Base
    # :equals tell the plugin to use "=" in SQL instead LIKE that is the default.
    acts_as_searchable :description, :size => :equals
  end
	
  # View
  # Put the search_form when you want to print the search form.
  <%= search_form %> 

